        "question": "<p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"> <span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Consider the following statements regarding the structure of Carnatic music compositions and choose correct option:</b></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Statement 1: Varnam is typically performed at the end of a Carnatic concert to summarize key ragas.</b></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Statement 2: Alapana involves improvisational elaboration of a raga without rhythm (tala).</b></span></span></span></span></p>",
